All done and pushed. Here's a summary of everything that was built:

What was added
3 new files
File	Purpose
coordinator.py	SpiderFarmerCoordinator — shared dict updated by both MQTT and BLE; fires HA entity callbacks on every change
ble_protocol.py	AES-128-CBC packet framing, CRC16-Modbus, all command factories (setLight, setFan, setBlower, setHeater, activation flow)
ble_coordinator.py	BLE connection loop: activation sequence, multi-fragment reassembly, send-with-retry/msgId matching, periodic polling, graceful reconnect
Bugs fixed vs reference implementation
Two bugs from doc/spider_farmer_ble/ were fixed:

Footer CRC accounting — outer_payload_len does NOT include the 2-byte footer; the reference left 2 junk bytes per packet causing log spam
Dynamic IV — correct value is raw[6:20] + 0x0000 (14 inner-header bytes + 2 zeros); the reference used raw[6:22] (included 2 ciphertext bytes instead)
Updated files
const.py — BLE UUIDs, packet constants, confirmed/candidate KEY/IV presets for CB (APK candidate), LED (confirmed), PS10 (confirmed)
manifest.json — v2.0.0, bleak-retry-connector requirement, bluetooth[] match rules for all SF-GGS-* names
config_flow.py — async_step_bluetooth for passive discovery; 3-step flow: MQTT → device picker (dropdown of nearby devices) → KEY/IV confirmation with auto-preset from advertising name
__init__.py — centralised MQTT subscriber; BLE startup; verbose DEBUG logging of every MQTT message and BLE lifecycle event for protocol tracing
sensor.py — adds CO₂, PPFD, soil temp/humidity/EC, firmware version (BLE-sourced)
light.py, fan.py, binary_sensor.py — all refactored to coordinator pattern; light/fan commands mirrored to BLE when connected
How parallel operation works
Both MQTT and BLE call coordinator.update(data_dict) which deep-merges into the same state dict. Whichever transport delivers data first (or most recently) wins for each key. Entities register one callback with the coordinator and never touch MQTT or BLE directly.



